RegisterGroup.name: CTI_NS
RegisterGroup.description: Cross-Trigger Interface control. NOTE: this is not a separate peripheral, but describes CM33 functionality.

Enum.name: Disabled
Enum.description: All cross-triggering mapping logic functionality is disabled.

Enum.name: Enabled
Enum.description: Cross-triggering mapping logic functionality is enabled.

BitField.name: APPCLEAR_0
BitField.description: Sets the corresponding bits in the CTIAPPSET to 0. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

BitField.name: APPCLEAR_1
BitField.description: Sets the corresponding bits in the CTIAPPSET to 0. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

BitField.name: APPCLEAR_2
BitField.description: Sets the corresponding bits in the CTIAPPSET to 0. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

BitField.name: APPCLEAR_3
BitField.description: Sets the corresponding bits in the CTIAPPSET to 0. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

BitField.name: APPULSE_0
BitField.description: Setting a bit HIGH generates a channel event pulse for the selected channel. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

Enum.name: Generate
Enum.description: Generates an event pulse on channel 0.

BitField.name: APPULSE_1
BitField.description: Setting a bit HIGH generates a channel event pulse for the selected channel. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

Enum.name: Generate
Enum.description: Generates an event pulse on channel 1.

BitField.name: APPULSE_2
BitField.description: Setting a bit HIGH generates a channel event pulse for the selected channel. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

Enum.name: Generate
Enum.description: Generates an event pulse on channel 2.

BitField.name: APPULSE_3
BitField.description: Setting a bit HIGH generates a channel event pulse for the selected channel. There is one bit of the register for each channel.

Enum.name: Generate
Enum.description: Generates an event pulse on channel 3.

Register.name: IFTIMING.RXDELAY
Register.description: Sample delay for input serial data on MISO

BitField.name: RXDELAY
BitField.description: Sample delay for input serial data on MISO. The value specifies the number of 64 MHz clock cycles (15.625 ns) delay from the the sampling edge of SCK (leading edge for CONFIG.CPHA = 0, trailing edge for CONFIG.CPHA = 1) until the input serial data is sampled. As en example, if RXDELAY = 0 and CONFIG.CPHA = 0, the input serial data is sampled on the rising edge of SCK.

Register.name: IFTIMING.CSNDUR
Register.description: Minimum duration between edge of CSN and edge of SCK. When SHORTS.END_START is used, this is also the minimum duration CSN must stay high between transactions.

BitField.name: CSNDUR
BitField.description: Minimum duration between edge of CSN and edge of SCK. When SHORTS.END_START is used, this is the minimum duration CSN must stay high between transactions. The value is specified in number of 64 MHz clock cycles (15.625 ns).

BitField.name: DCXCNT
BitField.description: This register specifies the number of command bytes preceding the data bytes. The PSEL.DCX line will be low during transmission of command bytes and high during transmission of data bytes. Value 0xF indicates that all bytes are command bytes.

BitField.name: RELOAD

BitField.description: The current value of the SysTick counter

BitField.name: TENMS
BitField.description: Reload value for 10ms (100Hz) timing, subject to system clock skew errors

BitField.description: Indicates whether the TENMS value is exact

BitField.name: NOREF
BitField.description: Indicates whether the device provides a reference clock to the processor

BitField.description: The total number of interrupt lines supported by an implementation, defined in groups of 32.

BitField.name: DISMCYCINT
BitField.description: When set to 1, disables interruption of load multiple and store multiple instructions

BitField.name: DISFOLD
BitField.description: When set to 1, dual-issue functionality is disabled

BitField.name: DISOOFP
BitField.description: Disables floating-point instructions completing out of order with respect to non-floating-point instructions

BitField.name: EXTEXCLALL
BitField.description: LDREX and STREX instructions always use the Global Exclusive Monitor

Register.name: CPPWR
Register.description: Specifies whether coprocessors are permitted to enter a non-retentive power state

BitField.name: RETTOBASE
BitField.description: Indicates whether there are preempted active exceptions

BitField.name: VECTPENDING
BitField.description: Indicates the exception number of the highest priority pending enabled exception

Register.name: AIRCR
Register.description: Application Interrupt and Reset Control Register

BitField.name: BFHFNMINS
BitField.description: BusFault and NMI are Non-secure and exceptions can target Non-secure HardFault

BitField.name: SLEEPONEXIT
BitField.description: Indicates sleep-on-exit when returning from Handler mode to Thread mode

BitField.name: SLEEPDEEP
BitField.description: Controls whether the processor uses sleep or deep sleep as its low power mode

BitField.name: SLEEPDEEPS
BitField.description: The SLEEPDEEP bit behaves as RAZ/WI when accessed from the Non-secure state

BitField.name: NONBASETHRDENA
BitField.description: Indicates how the processor enters Thread mode

BitField.name: USERSETMPEND
BitField.description: Enables unprivileged software access to the STIR

BitField.name: DIV_0_TRP
BitField.description: Enables faulting or halting when the processor executes an SDIVor UDIV instruction with a divisor of 0

BitField.name: BFHFNMIGN
BitField.description: Enables handlers with priority -1 or-2 to ignore data BusFaults caused by load and store instructions

BitField.name: STKALIGN
BitField.description: Indicates stack alignment on exception entry

BitField.name: STKOFHFNMIGN
BitField.description: Stack limit faults at requested priorities of less than 0 ignored

Register.name: SHCSR
Register.description: System Handler Control and State Register

BitField.name: MUNSTKERR
BitField.description: MemManage fault on unstacking for a return from exception

BitField.name: MSTKERR
BitField.description: MemManage fault on stacking for exception entry

BitField.name: MLSPERR
BitField.description: Indicates a MemManage fault occurred during floating-point lazy state preservation

BitField.name: MMARVALID

BitField.name: UNSTKERR
BitField.description: BusFault on unstacking for a return from exception

BitField.name: LSPERR
